reviewText: I just finished watching the movie Ride a Crooked Trail and I have to admit the movie is very enjoyable to watch. The dvd quality is excellent and I would recommend the movie to anyone who enjoys a good action packed western. The confilcts which occur in the movie can really speak for themselves when people are at a crossroads with decisions they need to make in life. A truly entertaining film.
summary: plays perfect. A joy to watch

reviewText: I grew up watching Audie in about all his westerns and enjoyed them all. Not only was Audie a war hero but a western hero also. Audie was one of those who gave it his best it seemed to me like. You also have to like westerns to enjoy this movie, as for me it is hard to enjoy a western made today. Back in the 50's & 60's I tried to watch all the westerns available on black & white TV. Now you can buy about all of them that you missed out on because of only 3 channels.

reviewText: the opening credits and theme song are banal - but then it opens upon a chase scene - before settling into a town run by - get this - Walter Matthau - that's how you can tell you're in for a offbeat treati saw this film as a kid - and i still remember the scene where the wounded Matthau walks off - with Murphy asking "Why doesn't he fall down"the script is jokey - but with a lot of fresh twists - the story breaks a new trail - one that Audie had never been down beforethis has perhaps Audie's best supporting cast - and that helps make this one of Murphy's best westerns - besides Matthau - there's gorgeous Gia Scala making the most of the 2-dimensional role of Murphy's faux wife - slimey Henry Silva as the baddie - and pretty Joanna Moore in a small role of a dance hall girl - seeing her and Gia face off is as good as any gunfightfun and interesting - this is not a B western - it's a B+ one
Title: N/A

reviewText: Ya gotta love an Audie Murphy movie!  I love Audie Murphy movies.  My top three cowboy heros; John Wayne, Jimmy Stewart and Audie Murphy.  Ya just can't get any better.This flick is another good cowboy movie that Audie did.  It doesn't matter what the plot is...Audie did the acting in his own great way and got the bad guy, won the girl and saved the day.  Ya just can't get much better.  Cookie cutters in this case... are not important.  It's  Audie.  Ya gotta love the guy and this movie.  Go buy it.  It will make you feel good.
